radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid filled and measuring up to 18 mm in caliber with an appendicolith seen within it. Mild fat stranding in the region. The visualized portion of the lung bases are unremarkable. The liver shows no intrahepatic biliary dilatation or focal lesion. The gallbladder shows no stones or wall edema. The spleen is normal. The pancreas and adrenal glands show no masses. The kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically. The abdomen shows no evidence of wall thickening or obstruction. The bladder, prostate, and rectum appear unremarkable with trace free fluid but no lymphadenopathy. No aggressive-appearing lytic or sclerotic lesions in bones.
